Task 2
Now we need the ribbon needed in total. Both around the package, and for the bow.
The length need for the wrapping is the sum of all three dimensions, minus the largest value. And multiply by 2:
We write a function for that:

wrap &lt;- function(x){
  2*(sum(x) - max(x))
}

Then theres the ribbon. For some undisclosed reason, that is simply the product of the dimensions. Weâ€™re not going to write a function for that.
We already have the input with a list column, dimensions, with numericial vectors.
We mutate two new columns into existence, the ribbon is the product, the wrap is found using our function from before:

input &lt;- input %&gt;% 
  mutate(ribbon = map(dimensions, prod)) %&gt;% 
  mutate(wrap = map(dimensions, wrap))
input

